Social Media aide to President Muhammadu Buhari, Bashir Ahmad has said that Abba Kyari was one of the most misunderstood persons in the history of Nigeria. Ahmad, while mourning the death  of Buhari’s Chief of Staff said Kyari, as opposed to opinions in Nigeria, sacrificed his life for Nigeria. Kyari died after battling Coronavirus. According to Ahmad, those that had the opportunity to meet him got to know his real personality. He described Kyari as a man of honour. On his Twitter page, he wrote: “Abba Kyari certainly was one of the most misunderstood people in the history of Nigeria. “ Those who had the opportunity to know him personally will tell you how extremely a good person he was. “A man of honour, will be remembered as someone who sacrificed his life for this country. “It was Mallam Abba Kyari’s turn last night, my time and your time will definitely come no matter how long it may take. And none of us will be here and healthy in the next 150 years.”